 "components": {
  "instruction": "Classify the given text into one of these categories: B, C, D, E, F, G, I, J, K.\n\nThe input will be a multiple choice question about what shape an SVG path element draws, with options labeled (A) through (J).\n\nYour response must be ONLY a single letter from the allowed categories (B, C, D, E, F, G, I, J, K). Do not include any explanation, analysis, or additional text whatsoever.\n\nTo determine the correct answer:\n1. Parse the SVG path commands (M = move to, L = line to)\n2. Count the number of distinct vertices/points in the path\n3. Each coordinate pair (x,y) after M or L represents a vertex\n4. If the path returns to the starting point, do not double-count it\n5. Match the vertex count to the corresponding shape option\n6. Return only the letter corresponding to that shape from the allowed categories\n\nShape to vertex count mapping:\n- 3 distinct points = triangle (J)\n- 4 distinct points = kite (D) or rectangle (not in allowed set)\n- 5 distinct points = pentagon (G)\n- 6 distinct points = hexagon (C)\n- 7 distinct points = heptagon (B)\n- 8 distinct points = octagon (F)\n\nAdditional notes:\n- The path may have multiple segments separated by M commands\n- Count all unique coordinate pairs across all path segments\n- Line (E), sector (I), and K are also valid response options depending on the shape\n- Only respond with one of these letters: B, C, D, E, F, G, I, J, or K\n- Do not provide any reasoning, explanation, parsing steps, or additional text in your response\n- Your entire response must be exactly one letter\n\nCritical: The assistant in the example started explaining their process instead of providing only the answer letter. This violates the core requirement. Always output ONLY the single letter answer, nothing else."
